<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Login Page</title>
  <link href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link href="styles.css">
  <style>
    body,
   .gradient-custom-2 {
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #075713, #0019fe) !important;
  }
  </style>
</head>

<body>

  <nav class="navbar navbar-dark bg-dark navbar-expand-lg mb-5">
    <div class="container">
      <a class="navbar-brand" href="/">My Application</a>
      <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#navbarNavDropdown" aria-controls="navbarNavDropdown" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle navigation">
        <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
      </button>
      <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarNavDropdown">
        <ul class="navbar-nav mr-auto">
          <li class="nav-item">
            <a class="nav-link" href="/">Home</a>
          </li>
          <li class="nav-item">
            <a class="nav-link" href="/Patients/Create">Create Patient</a>
          </li>
          <li class="nav-item">
            <a class="nav-link" href="/Patients/Details">Patient Details</a>
          </li>
          <% if(locals.user && locals.user.role === 'Admin') { %>
          <li class="nav-item">
            <a class="nav-link" href="/users">Users</a>
          </li>
          <% } %>
        </ul>
        <ul class="navbar-nav">
          <% if (locals.user) { %>
          <li class="nav-item">
            <a class="nav-link" href="/accounts/logout">Logout</a>
          </li>
          <%} else { %>
          <li class="nav-item">
            <a class="nav-link" href="/accounts/login">Log in</a>
          </li>
          <% } %>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <section class="h-100 gradient-form">
    <div class="container py-5 h-100">
      <div class="row d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center h-100">
        <div class="col-lg-10">
          <div class="card rounded-3 text-black">
            <div class="row g-0">
              <div class="col-lg-6">
                <div class="card-body p-md-5 mx-md-4">
                  <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="https://mdbcdn.b-cdn.net/img/Photos/new-templates/bootstrap-login-form/lotus.webp" style="width: 185px;" alt="logo">
                    <h4 class="mt-1 mb-5 pb-1">GenoTech Dynamics</h4>
                  </div>
            
                  <form action="/accounts/login" method="post">
                    <% if (message.length > 0) { %>
                    <div class="alert alert-danger">
                      <%= message %>
                    </div>
                    <% } %>
                    <div class="form-outline mb-4">
                      <input type="text" class="form-control" name="email" placeholder="Email" required>
                      <label class="form-label" for="form2Example11"></label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-outline mb-4">
                      <input type="password" class="form-control" name="password" placeholder="Password" required>
                      <label class="form-label" for="form2Example22"></label>
                    </div>
                    <button class="btn btn-warning btn-lg" type="submit">Login</button>
                  </form>
                  <hr>
                  <p>Don't have an account? <a href="/accounts/signup">Sign Up</a></p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-lg-6 d-flex align-items-center gradient-custom-2">
                <div class="text-white px-3 py-4 p-md-5 mx-md-4">
                  <h4 class="mb-4">Welcome to my Interactive Lab Management Platform</h4>
                  <p class="small mb-0">The initial step upon accessing the platform is to register your account. During the signup process, users are prompted to specify their role. If registered as an Admin, you gain exclusive privileges to create, modify, and delete user accounts within the system. Other role designations restrict access to the user management section.

                    This interactive lab platform empowers users to create patient profiles and manage their health status efficiently. It offers the flexibility to update or remove patient data as needed. Moreover, an option is available to conveniently download patient information into an Excel file for further analysis or reference.
                    
                    Furthermore, ongoing enhancements are underway to transform the lab interface into a more intuitive and user-friendly system. Expect continuous improvements as new features are being incorporated to enhance usability and functionality.Additionally, this platform operates in conjunction with a MongoDB database. MongoDB serves as the underlying database system supporting the Interactive Lab Management Platform. Leveraging MongoDB's capabilities, the platform efficiently stores and manages the vast array of patient records, workflow details, and other essential data. This database integration ensures robust data handling, scalability, and seamless performance for the entire lab management system</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.5.1.slim.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@popperjs/core@2.10.2/dist/umd/popper.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>

</body>

</html>
